Ever been tempted to sign off an email with, ‘FTW?’ Don’t. To slightly nerdy American cheer-leader types it means ‘For The Win,’ a sort of rabble-rousing pay off for those who’d use ‘Carpe Diem’ if they’d only ever heard of Latin. But to Biker Gangs it means, ‘F*** The World’ and – one I happen to love – it symbolises the more common, ‘What The F***?’ but in an intentional mis-spelling to emphasise confusion and bewilderment. I do hope that Miliband’s advisors don’t know the nuances.
